$ %ProgramFiles(x86)\Microsoft Visual Studio\version

This directory's → Windows/dirs/Program-Files-x86/Microsoft-Visual-Studio/version/edition[subdirectories] contain the installation roots
of the different editions that are installed for a specific → Windows/development/Visual-Studio[Visual Studio] version, such as
  • Community
  • Professional
  • Enterprise
  • TeamExplorer
  • BuildTools
  • ? TestAgent ?
  • ? TestController ?
  • … ?


Apparently, an edition is sometimes also referred to as *offering*.
